<subSubSection pageNumber="586" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="586">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="586">Note:</emphasis>
As noted by Villarrubia &amp; Moreno (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="586">Acta Bot. Malac.</emphasis>
17: 127. 1992), Linnaeus believed, on the authority of Clusius, that this taxon came from the Savoie Alps in France, but this is erroneous, the species in fact occurring in Greece, Turkey, Crete and Algeria. Moreno designated an 
<typeStatus>epitype</typeStatus>
in order to clarify the discrepancy in distribution.
</paragraph>
